♪The boat drifts, bringing back the sunset♪

89
00:07:33,400 --> 00:07:39,840
♪When we reunite, we still joke
about the cause and effect♪

90
00:07:40,530 --> 00:07:46,760
♪Who passed by,
the crabapple falls with a turn♪

91
00:07:47,900 --> 00:07:50,950
♪Loving rightly but choosing wrong♪

92
00:07:51,530 --> 00:07:56,030
♪With joys, sorrows, partings and reunions♪

93
00:07:56,660 --> 00:08:03,360
♪Everyone travels far, seeing clouds and snow♪

94
00:08:04,110 --> 00:08:07,770
♪Always hard to stay, yet easy to part♪

95
00:08:07,770 --> 00:08:11,230
♪Crossing spring waters and autumn trials♪

96
00:08:11,230 --> 00:08:17,960
♪A couple under the moonlight,
can stay together♪

97
00:08:18,320 --> 00:08:25,100
♪Time flows as we dream through four seasons♪

98
00:08:25,480 --> 00:08:31,470
♪I wish to journey with you forever♪

99
00:08:33,980 --> 00:08:38,210
♪Year after year♪

100
00:08:46,000 --> 00:08:47,070
Last night...

101
00:08:48,760 --> 00:08:49,600
Jiu.

102
00:08:53,720 --> 00:08:54,700
Mrs. Cui, are you alright?

103
00:08:55,210 --> 00:08:56,050
It's okay.

104
00:08:56,480 --> 00:08:58,290
You've seemed unwell since yesterday.

105
00:08:58,290 --> 00:08:59,860
Should we have Physician Zhao take a look?

106
00:09:00,290 --> 00:09:01,130
No need.

107
00:09:01,450 --> 00:09:02,980
I'm just a bit tired.

108
00:09:03,290 --> 00:09:04,390
Don't worry.

109
00:09:06,360 --> 00:09:07,200
Since you're tired,

110
00:09:07,810 --> 00:09:08,650
have some rest.

111
00:09:09,240 --> 00:09:10,740
I need to go to the porcelain shop.

112
00:09:11,050 --> 00:09:11,930
Remember?

113
00:09:11,930 --> 00:09:13,390
I'll take care of everything.

114
00:09:14,600 --> 00:09:15,510
Just kidding.

115
00:09:16,290 --> 00:09:17,670
Mrs. Cui is serious.

116
00:09:18,210 --> 00:09:19,330
Up before dawn,

117
00:09:19,330 --> 00:09:20,600
she started working on porcelain,

118
00:09:20,600 --> 00:09:21,860
looking worn out.

119
00:09:22,360 --> 00:09:23,570
Don't listen to her.

120
00:09:23,570 --> 00:09:24,670
I just didn't sleep well.

121
00:09:28,810 --> 00:09:29,650
Miantang,

122
00:09:30,760 --> 00:09:31,600
thank you.

123
00:09:46,760 --> 00:09:47,600
Jiu.

124
00:09:48,640 --> 00:09:51,210
You don't need to worry about money.

125
00:09:51,210 --> 00:09:52,360
As long as I win at Go,

126
00:09:52,360 --> 00:09:53,670
I'll give the money to you.

127
00:09:59,720 --> 00:10:00,620
Is... Is it...

128
00:10:01,690 --> 00:10:02,860
Is it too less?

129
00:10:07,480 --> 00:10:08,690
Then I will

130
00:10:08,690 --> 00:10:10,030
win more from now on.

131
00:10:43,930 --> 00:10:44,840
Liu Miantang wants to

132
00:10:44,840 --> 00:10:45,860
handle everything for you?

133
00:10:47,090 --> 00:10:48,360
She probably thinks

134
00:10:48,360 --> 00:10:49,570
I'm a useless

135
00:10:49,570 --> 00:10:51,310
good-for-nothing.

136
00:10:51,600 --> 00:10:52,740
What did you say?

137
00:10:54,450 --> 00:10:55,410
What could I say?

138
00:10:55,410 --> 00:10:56,740
There's nothing to argue about.

139
00:10:57,760 --> 00:10:59,310
She's a bit high-maintenance

140
00:10:59,720 --> 00:11:01,330
but still organized.

141
00:11:01,330 --> 00:11:02,190
I'll let her be.

142
00:11:04,240 --> 00:11:05,670
You don't care to argue with her?

143
00:11:08,170 --> 00:11:09,970
I think you enjoy this, don't you?

144
00:11:10,880 --> 00:11:11,860
Cui Xingzhou, listen up.

145
00:11:12,930 --> 00:11:14,120
No one in this world

146
00:11:14,120 --> 00:11:15,460
truly shares

147
00:11:15,690 --> 00:11:17,820
your worries except me.

148
00:11:23,290 --> 00:11:25,340
Enemies like wolves from afar,

149
00:11:26,050 --> 00:11:28,030
women like foxes close by.

150
00:11:28,410 --> 00:11:30,700
You've living in constant vigilance.

151
00:11:31,760 --> 00:11:32,600
Now,

152
00:11:33,760 --> 00:11:35,510
a beautiful girl appears.

153
00:11:36,360 --> 00:11:37,790
She asks for nothing

154
00:11:38,240 --> 00:11:39,600
and wants nothing,

155
00:11:39,600 --> 00:11:41,550
but trusts you completely

156
00:11:42,570 --> 00:11:44,550
and loves and cares for you the most.

157
00:11:46,120 --> 00:11:47,150
If it were me,

158
00:11:47,450 --> 00:11:49,550
I'd rather be a good-for-nothing too,

159
00:11:51,330 --> 00:11:52,860
even though I'm already one.

160
00:11:57,450 --> 00:11:58,820
Didn't realize

161
00:11:59,480 --> 00:12:00,910
you had a flair for drama.

162
00:12:04,240 --> 00:12:05,910
Could you really kill

163
00:12:06,330 --> 00:12:07,460
such a good woman?

164
00:12:11,210 --> 00:12:12,330
Honestly,

165
00:12:12,330 --> 00:12:14,910
a woman like her

166
00:12:15,810 --> 00:12:17,410
escaping from that den of thieves

167
00:12:17,410 --> 00:12:19,070
has it hard.

168
00:12:20,090 --> 00:12:22,100
Lu Wen has many enemies.

169
00:12:23,120 --> 00:12:25,270
She was left alone and had her tendons cut.

170
00:12:26,600 --> 00:12:28,050
Maybe I should let her go.

171
00:12:28,050 --> 00:12:28,940
Exactly.

172
00:12:30,840 --> 00:12:32,510
The Liu family committed crimes,

173
00:12:33,050 --> 00:12:34,620
so she's homeless.

174
00:12:34,930 --> 00:12:36,580
She's also tainted

175
00:12:36,970 --> 00:12:38,460
and shunned by society.

176
00:12:41,640 --> 00:12:43,150
I should pity

177
00:12:45,210 --> 00:12:47,340
for her innocent suffering.

178
00:12:47,760 --> 00:12:49,310
What if

179
00:12:49,970 --> 00:12:52,330
she helps me catch the thief...

180
00:12:52,330 --> 00:12:53,510
What will you do?

181
00:12:56,120 --> 00:12:57,670
I'll give her some money,

182
00:12:58,640 --> 00:12:59,720
send her to a temple,

183
00:12:59,720 --> 00:13:00,760
and let her live peacefully.

184
00:13:00,760 --> 00:13:01,600
And you!

185
00:13:02,640 --> 00:13:04,190
Don't go see her,

186
00:13:05,170 --> 00:13:07,460
or rumors will spread.

187
00:13:11,760 --> 00:13:12,600
Did you hear me?

188
00:13:15,500 --> 00:13:17,980
(Rice)

189
00:13:21,360 --> 00:13:22,200
Mrs. Cui.

190
00:13:23,720 --> 00:13:25,100
Peers can be tough on each other.

191
00:13:25,600 --> 00:13:26,940
We'd better not go.

192
00:13:27,930 --> 00:13:29,760
Why don't we sit here

193
00:13:29,760 --> 00:13:30,600
and have some tea?

194
00:13:32,840 --> 00:13:33,680
Shopkeeper,

195
00:13:34,050 --> 00:13:34,890
tea, please.

196
00:13:35,210 --> 00:13:36,050
Coming.

197
00:13:40,260 --> 00:13:41,420
(He's Porcelain Shop)

198
00:13:41,450 --> 00:13:42,290
Watch the steps.

199
00:13:42,290 --> 00:13:43,190
Easy, sir.

200
00:13:43,410 --> 00:13:44,250
Nanny Li,

201
00:13:44,640 --> 00:13:45,580
look at those two.

202
00:13:46,810 --> 00:13:48,450
They're tanned,

203
00:13:48,450 --> 00:13:49,930
and their waist pouches full.

204
00:13:49,930 --> 00:13:51,220
They came in our shop

205
00:13:51,520 --> 00:13:53,310
and found the best items right away,

206
00:13:53,880 --> 00:13:55,980
which shows they're regular porcelain traders.

207
00:13:57,240 --> 00:13:58,790
But they don't buy anything here.

208
00:13:59,520 --> 00:14:00,790
I want to see

209
00:14:01,520 --> 00:14:02,860
what experts

210
00:14:03,930 --> 00:14:05,150
consider valuable.

211
00:14:05,760 --> 00:14:07,410
- How about this one?
- Not bad.

212
00:14:07,410 --> 00:14:09,330
Next time you get new stock, let me know.

213
00:14:09,330 --> 00:14:10,720
I'll notify you immediately.

214
00:14:10,720 --> 00:14:11,560
See you, sir.

215
00:14:12,000 --> 00:14:12,940
Ma'am, come on in.

216
00:14:15,610 --> 00:14:16,520
We have

217
00:14:16,520 --> 00:14:17,940
the finest porcelain.

218
00:14:18,210 --> 00:14:19,570
Take a look and see if you like any.

219
00:14:19,570 --> 00:14:20,620
I'll introduce them to you.

220
00:14:30,450 --> 00:14:31,880
You have a good eye, ma'am.

221
00:14:31,880 --> 00:14:32,930
This piece is made by our

222
00:14:32,930 --> 00:14:33,940
most experienced craftsman.

223
00:14:34,240 --> 00:14:35,080
Really?

224
00:14:36,170 --> 00:14:37,810
But I've seen this kiln technique

225
00:14:37,810 --> 00:14:39,480
in other shops.

226
00:14:39,480 --> 00:14:40,510
It's nothing special.

227
00:14:40,760 --> 00:14:41,600
Well...

228
00:14:45,330 --> 00:14:46,580
How about you check out some others?

229
00:14:48,330 --> 00:14:49,170
Ma.

230
00:14:51,000 --> 00:14:53,310
Ma'am, you can check inside.

231
00:14:54,330 --> 00:14:55,860
These are all fine pieces.

232
00:15:02,090 --> 00:15:02,940
Look.

233
00:15:03,240 --> 00:15:04,270
How about this set?

234
00:15:04,570 --> 00:15:05,790
It's delicate.

235
00:15:09,880 --> 00:15:10,980
What's this seal?

236
00:15:11,690 --> 00:15:12,530
Give it to me.

237
00:15:13,240 --> 00:15:14,080
Ma'am.

238
00:15:14,170 --> 00:15:15,980
You can look, but please don't touch.

239
00:15:16,880 --> 00:15:17,790
This seal

240
00:15:18,000 --> 00:15:19,460
means it's from an official kiln,

241
00:15:19,760 --> 00:15:21,220
made for the royal family.

242
00:15:21,450 --> 00:15:23,030
If it weren't for a flaw,

243
00:15:23,520 --> 00:15:24,620
you wouldn't

244
00:15:24,880 --> 00:15:26,070
be seeing it today.

245
00:15:26,930 --> 00:15:28,930
Other shops are empty,

246
00:15:28,930 --> 00:15:30,340
but yours is bustling

247
00:15:31,090 --> 00:15:32,100
because of these royal items.

248
00:15:32,410 --> 00:15:33,910
We are not the only ones selling these.

249
00:15:34,170 --> 00:15:36,640
Ma'am, you must be new here

250
00:15:36,640 --> 00:15:38,460
and unfamiliar with the market.

251
00:15:39,290 --> 00:15:40,210
So,

252
00:15:40,210 --> 00:15:41,100
just as a reminder,

253
00:15:41,570 --> 00:15:44,820
you buy from shops with trade guild plaques.

254
00:15:45,570 --> 00:15:46,410
Trade guild?

255
00:15:46,480 --> 00:15:47,320
Yes.

256
00:15:47,520 --> 00:15:49,060
There are 12 members in town,

257
00:15:49,060 --> 00:15:50,020
(Porcelain)

258
00:15:50,020 --> 00:15:51,860
with established brands,

259
00:15:52,240 --> 00:15:53,330
mutually guaranteed,

260
00:15:53,330 --> 00:15:54,390
and well-known.

261
00:15:56,210 --> 00:15:57,210
(Porcelain)
As for small,

262
00:15:57,240 --> 00:15:59,310
unregistered trade guild workshops,

263
00:15:59,810 --> 00:16:01,290
I advise you

264
00:16:01,290 --> 00:16:02,910
to avoid them.

265
00:16:03,840 --> 00:16:05,340
In Lingquan Town,

266
00:16:05,600 --> 00:16:06,970
newcomers

267
00:16:06,970 --> 00:16:09,100
who don't know this

268
00:16:09,480 --> 00:16:11,430
won't succeed in their business.

269
00:16:13,090 --> 00:16:14,360
Since that's the case,

270
00:16:14,360 --> 00:16:15,720
I'll buy this bowl.

271
00:16:15,720 --> 00:16:16,620
- Okay.
- How much is it?

272
00:16:17,170 --> 00:16:18,010
One tael of gold.

273
00:16:18,410 --> 00:16:19,250
One tael of gold?

274
00:16:20,760 --> 00:16:21,840
I don't have

275
00:16:21,840 --> 00:16:23,150
that much.

276
00:16:23,980 --> 00:16:25,640
Could you please

277
00:16:25,640 --> 00:16:26,480
lower the price?

278
00:16:26,970 --> 00:16:28,330
He's Porcelain

279
00:16:28,330 --> 00:16:30,150
is top-notch and worth the price.

280
00:16:30,450 --> 00:16:31,550
I can't decide.

281
00:16:33,000 --> 00:16:34,620
Miss He is right there.

282
00:16:35,090 --> 00:16:36,840
Just be kind to her,

283
00:16:36,840 --> 00:16:37,940
and then you can decide.

284
00:16:38,690 --> 00:16:39,760
How do you know

285
00:16:39,760 --> 00:16:40,700
who I am?

286
00:16:43,360 --> 00:16:44,640
When I entered,

287
00:16:44,640 --> 00:16:46,640
the shopkeeper was focused
on the accounts,

288
00:16:46,640 --> 00:16:49,000
glancing at you

289
00:16:49,000 --> 00:16:50,480
rather than the customers.

290
00:16:50,480 --> 00:16:52,210
Clearly, you're here to oversee the books.

291
00:16:52,210 --> 00:16:54,330
The shopkeeper couldn't tend to the customers,

292
00:16:54,330 --> 00:16:55,620
